    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>So the solution to the original problem is that you don't need both the \"@see\" and the \"{@link...}\" references on the same line.  The \"@link\" tag is self-sufficient and, as noted, you can put it anywhere in the javadoc block. So you can mix the two approaches:</p>\n\n<pre><code>/**\n * some javadoc stuff\n * {@link com.my.package.Class#method()}\n * more stuff\n * @see com.my.package.AnotherClass\n */\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
